## Introduction
This project explores the field of anthropometrics and ergonomics, focusing on the measurement of human body dimensions and their application in designing products, workspaces, and systems that optimize human well-being and overall system performance. The study involves collecting data on various body measurements, analyzing ergonomic principles, and applying these insights to improve design processes.

The project aims to enhance user comfort, safety, and efficiency by integrating anthropometric data into design considerations. Through this work, we seek to contribute to the development of more user-centered designs that accommodate a diverse range of human body types and capabilities.

